shooting cracks in the snow or the newly drifted slab feels hard or hollow underneath. Use extra caution on exposed slopes or in extreme terrain where small slides can have big consequences. Look for sheltered slopes with no slab, or slopes less than about 35 degrees, as safer options.<\/p><p>Spring snow can stick to very steep slopes as it falls. If the sun shows its face tomorrow, expect the new snow to sluff off very steep slopes and slopes with lots of rocks or cliffs.<\/p><hr><p><em>Researchers Ian McCammon and Sara Boilen are developing new tools for managing human factors for&nbsp;backcountry skiers and boarders. This survey asks about personal experiences with human factors and will take 7 - 8 minutes to fill out.&nbsp;<\/em><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https:\/\/eoustmhs.qualtrics.com\/jfe\/form\/SV_exIaG7ZwFaA9lOK\"><em>Link is&nbsp;HERE.<\/em><\/a><em>&nbsp;Thank you for your help!<\/em><\/p>"}]},"terrainAndTravelAdvice":{"days":[[],[],[]]},"communication":{"headline":"","sms":""},"media":{"Images":[{"id":"34bb77cd-62d8-48ce-b740-05c6949d7aff","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1776110020\/AvIDfx\/gckcdotmzhsenynvw4vj.webp","width":350,"height":263,"credit":"","caption":"<p>This image is a good example of the kind of terrain and type of avalanche you can trigger on Wednesday and Thursday as the wind drifts snow into slabs. You can see it's a relatively thin slab just below a corniced ridge, inside a couloir.<\/p>","tag":"avalanche","altText":"An avalanche below a corniced ridge, inside a couloir.","dateTaken":"2026-04-08T19:53:53.695Z","isArchived":false},{"id":"7677e370-dfd5-4061-b2b5-682b0a86a829","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1776110151\/AvIDfx\/vpxmfzaoljnfopwyhlhv.webp","width":350,"height":263,"credit":"","caption":"<p>This avalanche from April 4th shows the type of terrain (and avalanche) you want to be careful of on Wednesday and Thursday.<\/p>","tag":"avalanche","altText":"Looking up at a small avalanche in a snow-filled couloir.","dateTaken":"2026-04-04T19:55:53.56Z","isArchived":false}]},"dangerRatings":{"days":[{"position":1,"alp":"moderate","tln":"low","btl":"low","date":"2026-04-15T22:30:00Z"},{"position":2,"alp":"moderate","tln":"low","btl":"low","date":"2026-04-16T22:30:00Z"},{"position":3,"alp":"moderate","tln":"low","btl":"low","date":"2026-04-17T22:30:00Z"}]},"avalancheProblems":{"days":[[{"type":"windSlab","aspectElevations":["n_alp","se_alp","e_alp","ne_alp"],"likelihood":"possible","expectedSize":{"min":"1.0","max":"1.5"}}],[{"type":"windSlab","aspectElevations":["n_alp","se_alp","e_alp","ne_alp"],"likelihood":"possible","expectedSize":{"min":"1.0","max":"1.5"}}],[{"type":"windSlab","aspectElevations":["n_alp","se_alp","e_alp","ne_alp"],"likelihood":"possible","expectedSize":{"min":"1.0","max":"1.5"}}]]}},{"id":"87baa31f-9153-4ee7-ae56-8a148cf77ec8","publicName":"120-121-129-130-131-132-133-134-135-138-141-142","type":"avalancheforecast","polygons":["288624C3-E0C0-4816-86A1-57B068E20D5F","568FD9F5-9079-4965-BD83-8DD1577C9141","674FEC54-6A25-4F1B-9201-B145C6C609E0","6BE87E45-0574-4512-907F-EC3B9EBCA365","93EA98DD-4165-4B8D-97F7-FE0774706466","98E60E8A-5124-454F-9660-9B879AE63B09","A3B7D9A2-121A-41EA-B824-ADCB4B1323A3","B4DBB658-8373-4DAB-8D42-7ABA0564AF9E","CB25CEAA-D3C0-416C-B11B-60B3BFF39F34","D6E3810F-1A94-4173-A5AD-147EEC39E464","D7362528-9E1C-4B04-ACEA-70E4F9BFB8B7","EEF9E8C9-3899-4E76-8A11-C2265812FA53"],"areaId":"74360d0cf4b424f4856bcc804d66c53de97fa8109f0a3250b0626901ca2a1891","forecaster":"Jeff Davis","issueDateTime":"2026-04-14T22:30:00Z","expiryDateTime":"2026-04-15T22:30:00Z","isTranslated":false,"isAutoTranslated":false,"isMultiDay":false,"timezone":"America\/Denver","weatherSummary":{"days":[]},"snowpackSummary":{"days":[]},"avalancheSummary":{"days":[{"date":"2026-04-15T22:30:00Z","content":"<p>New and drifted snow increase the chances of avalanches above treeline. The most dangerous areas will be very steep leeward slopes and rocky cross-loaded couloirs, where a small slab could wipe you off your feet and take you for a nasty ride. Look for and avoid obvious drifts, especially if traveling in extreme terrain. Cracking in the snow surface is an indication that you have found one of these drifts and highlights the need for you to assess the steep slopes you plan to travel. <\/p><p>As the new snow warms, we can expect a small shed cycle and loose avalanche to be triggered in the new snow on steep drifted slopes.<\/p><hr><p><em>Researchers Ian McCammon and Sara Boilen are developing new tools for managing human factors for&nbsp;<\/em><strong><em>backcountry skiers and boarders<\/em><\/strong><em>. This survey asks about personal experiences with human factors and will take 7 - 8 minutes to fill out. <\/em><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https:\/\/eoustmhs.qualtrics.com\/jfe\/form\/SV_exIaG7ZwFaA9lOK\"><em>Link is&nbsp;HERE.<\/em><\/a><em> Thank you for your help!<\/em><\/p>"}]},"terrainAndTravelAdvice":{"days":[[],[],[]]},"communication":{"headline":"","sms":""},"media":{"Images":[{"id":"cbfcfedd-e5fd-4b60-9f85-ef12f77086ce","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1776024571\/AvIDfx\/fmmnmthue7objvadytym.webp","width":2500,"height":1875,"credit":"","caption":"<p>This is a photo of snow coverage prior to Tuesday storm. There was still plenty on snow on high alpine north, northeast, and east slopes. Areas that have snow coverage are the best places to recreate, but will also be the places you can trigger avalanches. <\/p>","tag":"avalanche","altText":"Snow covered slope ","dateTaken":"2026-04-12T20:01:54.418Z","isArchived":false},{"id":"c6a11b8c-0fc8-4e65-b6e8-427c420c75c4","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1776196886\/AvIDfx\/sscbtmuvprgndtkzvhzs.webp","width":2500,"height":1667,"credit":"","caption":"<p>This small avalanche was observed on Kendall Mountain above Silverton during a brief break in weather on Tuesday. This is a good example of the types of avalanches you can trigger in the new snow. Although small, dangerous in the wrong terrain. Pay attention to how much snow and the slope angle of the slopes you play to ride. Steep, loaded, and a slick sliding surface are the keys to triggering avalanches. <\/p>","tag":"avalanche","altText":"Small avalanche on mountain ","dateTaken":"2026-04-14T20:01:30.004Z","isArchived":false},{"id":"ccef3e55-1acb-4449-9642-6020b27c535d","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1776200997\/AvIDfx\/glcrannbcsbjbya37bxy.webp","width":1600,"height":1204,"credit":"","caption":"<p>Drifted areas is where we could trigger the largest avalanches. In this photo you can see evidence of drifting just below ridgelines following Tuesdays storm. <\/p>","tag":"avalanche","altText":"Drifted areas of snow ","dateTaken":"2026-04-14T21:10:00.699Z","isArchived":false},{"id":"263fd0b3-66ca-4a76-856e-1ed5fc35c8a7","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1776201781\/AvIDfx\/l1zm2vpjlmzfstfcj4y6.webp","width":1204,"height":1600,"credit":"","caption":"<p>Cracking in the snow surface is an indication that you have found an area of drifted snow and highlights the need for you to assess the steep slopes you plan to travel.<\/p>","tag":"avalanche","altText":"ski with crack ","dateTaken":"2026-04-14T21:23:06.47Z","isArchived":false}]},"dangerRatings":{"days":[{"position":1,"alp":"moderate","tln":"low","btl":"low","date":"2026-04-15T22:30:00Z"},{"position":2,"alp":"moderate","tln":"low","btl":"low","date":"2026-04-16T22:30:00Z"},{"position":3,"alp":"low","tln":"low","btl":"low","date":"2026-04-17T22:30:00Z"}]},"avalancheProblems":{"days":[[{"type":"windSlab","aspectElevations":["n_alp","ne_alp","e_alp"],"likelihood":"possible","expectedSize":{"min":"1.0","max":"1.5"}}],[{"type":"windSlab","aspectElevations":["n_alp","ne_alp","e_alp"],"likelihood":"possible","expectedSize":{"min":"1.0","max":"1.5"}}],[]]}},{"id":"98a95f8c-43a9-420c-b2dc-374e8517c3e6","publicName":"139-140-143-144-145","type":"avalancheforecast","polygons":["242191AB-2749-4585-A09B-C274A1C196D8","428340C8-91A8-480A-8FB8-322EAB7CD9EB","ECA6DAA1-1E5C-4D1F-8186-B9969A5E9EAD","FCDD2204-2B10-4061-8CDF-928C5DE4C24D","FD36A9C3-DDBD-43BF-BA4B-AE2D2C8CA87F"],"areaId":"66c50e04e2286ea06aef0f5e3da9db0f575f18a3a95d505388ae1d3dddb16a37","forecaster":"Jeff Davis","issueDateTime":"2026-04-14T22:30:00Z","expiryDateTime":"2026-04-15T22:30:00Z","isTranslated":false,"isAutoTranslated":false,"isMultiDay":false,"timezone":"America\/Denver","weatherSummary":{"days":[]},"snowpackSummary":{"days":[]},"avalancheSummary":{"days":[{"date":"2026-04-15T22:30:00Z","content":"<p>Avalanche conditions are generally safe. In very steep or extreme terrain, use caution around newly drifted snow and watch for small sluffs. Even a small amount of moving snow can knock you off your feet and carry you into hazardous terrain further down the mountain.<\/p><hr><p><em>Researchers Ian McCammon and Sara Boilen are developing new tools for managing human factors for&nbsp;backcountry skiers and boarders. This survey asks about personal experiences with human factors and will take 7 - 8 minutes to fill out. <\/em><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https:\/\/eoustmhs.qualtrics.com\/jfe\/form\/SV_exIaG7ZwFaA9lOK\"><em>Link is&nbsp;HERE.<\/em><\/a><em> Thank you for your help!<\/em><\/p>"}]},"terrainAndTravelAdvice":{"days":[[],[],[]]},"communication":{"headline":"","sms":""},"media":{"Images":[{"id":"a9d45854-eb92-445a-9880-23c5feb3932e","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1776196313\/AvIDfx\/w7owhjq9hvvu8ktbrvqp.webp","width":2500,"height":3333,"credit":"","caption":"<p>If riding in steep terrain like this, manage your sluff so you don't get knocked down or swept into consequential terrain features.<\/p>","tag":"avalanche","altText":"Small sluff in steep gulley","dateTaken":"2026-04-14T19:51:59.173Z","isArchived":false},{"id":"e285ecc6-c15b-440f-bf53-62eedbf2fc60","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1775244557\/AvIDfx\/jywmvfljwdyuotowuk2d.webp","width":350,"height":263,"credit":"","caption":"<p>A skier triggered this avalanche in the Elk Mountains on April 2. While this avalanche is not large enough to bury a person, it could still take you for a dangerous ride if you are swept off your feet and down the slope.<\/p>","tag":"avalanche","altText":"An avalanche with tracks nearby","dateTaken":"2026-04-02T19:29:19.513Z","isArchived":false},{"id":"cbfcfedd-e5fd-4b60-9f85-ef12f77086ce","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1775419310\/AvIDfx\/yljwgp944lj1ma5fy6nd.webp","width":1204,"height":1600,"credit":"","caption":"<p>There are few areas where you may be able to trigger an avalanche. The most likey areas are in very steep terrain at the upper most elevations that have stayed cool since the April 1st storm. This avalanche triggered on April 3rd south of Red Mountain Pass is a good example of the size of avalanches and the steeper terrain you may encounter isolated pockets of wind-drifted snow.<\/p>","tag":"avalanche","altText":"A ski track leading into a small wind slab avalanche in terrain that appears steep, shallow, and rocky","dateTaken":"2026-04-03T20:01:54.418Z","isArchived":false}]},"dangerRatings":{"days":[{"position":1,"alp":"low","tln":"low","btl":"low","date":"2026-04-15T22:30:00Z"},{"position":2,"alp":"low","tln":"low","btl":"low","date":"2026-04-16T22:30:00Z"},{"position":3,"alp":"noRating","tln":"noRating","btl":"noRating","date":"2026-04-17T22:30:00Z"}]},"avalancheProblems":{"days":[[{"type":"windSlab","aspectElevations":["n_alp","ne_alp","e_alp","se_alp"],"likelihood":"unlikely","expectedSize":{"min":"1.0","max":"1.5"}}],[{"type":"windSlab","aspectElevations":["n_alp","ne_alp","e_alp","se_alp"],"likelihood":"unlikely","expectedSize":{"min":"1.0","max":"1.5"}}],[]]